The OSI Model

Layer 1: Physical Layer
-	Signaling, cabling, connectors.
-	This layer isn’t about protocols
-	If problem arise  - Fix cabling, run loopback tests, etc. 

Layer 2: Data Link Layer
-	Used to communicate between two devices on the network
-	Often refer as MAC address layer (Media access control address) hardware address of the particular adapter card.
-	Extended unique identifier

Layer 3: Network Layer
-	The “routing” layer – how to forward traffic
-	IP, router, packet

Layer 4: Transport Layer
-	The “post office” layer
-	TCP and UDP 

Layer 5: Session Layer
-	Start, stop, restart – communication management between devices
-	Control protocols, tunneling protocols

Layer 6: Presentation Layer
-	Character encoding
-	Application encryption (SSL/TLS)

Layer 7: Application Layer
-	The layer we see (HTTP, FTP, DNS, POP3)
